CONTEXT Test IN ENGLISH

PATTERN Test4
RELATION r[X*Y]
RELATION s[X*A]
RELATION t[B*Y]
CLASSIFY B ISA E
CLASSIFY A ISA E
-- CLASSIFY D ISA B
-- CLASSIFY D ISA A
RULE r = s;t
ENDPATTERN

ENDCONTEXT

{-
   Purpose: This script demonstrates how NOT to specify an intersection type D between A and B.
   Result: Fail
   Reason: the intersection between A and B should exists for s;t to be well-typed.
-}